  "original_title": "3 \u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bb2\u0b95 \u0b95\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd : \u0baa\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbe\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0b9a\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bb0\u0bcd, \u0b87\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0bc1\u0bb5 \u0ba4\u0bb3\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0bae\u0bc7\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc8 !",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Presidential Secretariat doors to be opened after 3 months : Defense Secretary, Army Chief Supervised !",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "Colombo - The operations of the Fort Presidential Secretariat will resume to normal from today, Monday, the 25th.",
        "Since last April 9, the main entrance of the Presidential Secretariat (Gate Zero) has been blocked and vandalized by the empty-faced Kota Ko Kama protesters, and it has been announced that the secretariat activities are limited.",
        "In this situation, after the seizure of the Presidential Secretariat by millions of people who gathered in Colombo on July 9, the activities of the Secretariat were completely paralyzed.",
        "In this situation, on the morning of Friday 22nd, the armed forces attacked and chased the protestors in front of the presidential secretariat and brought the secretariat under their control.",
        "While the damaged doors and windows of the Secretariat were reconstructed on the afternoon of the 24th, a senior official of the Presidential Secretariat said that it is planned to resume normal operations from today.",
        "On the afternoon of the 24th, Defense Secretary General Kamal Gunaratna and Army Commander Lt. Gen. Vikum Lienake visited the Presidential Secretariat and personally confirmed all matters including the security situation. In this situation, the secretariat activities will be carried out as usual from today."
      ],
